I do not see a value of this app. There are more advanced tools to log cell network info. Buying a PRO version for ability to log best and avg. signal values with Lat/Lon and only CID+LAC is not enough in my opinion.  At least if the log contained worst signal value during the requested time window and if it contained meadian of the signal (not average). I also miss MCC, MNC, UCID RNC/eNBi. More "compressed" logging would be welcome. For example, log only if I change network connection mode or even a provider or move more than 500m away. Otherwise just sum up collected data points into a single row in the logile. ifailed to find where does the tower location DB come from, but it should be emphasized those values are supposedly calculated based on measurements of user from around the world (hence incomplete a most towers around me are in totally wrong places). There are better tools: Netmonster (pro CZ, PL at least with curated database of towers), Network Cell Info (buy PRO!), Netmonitor (logs only changes), Cell Coverage Map. If you want to contribute public databases install Tower Collector, Cellmapper, Mozlla Stumbler. For Wifi/Ethernet info install Net analyzer from J. Techet.

If  your Samsung Galaxy wont run Signal strength widgets, I have stumbled on an easy work around that works for me and may work for you! Simply go to the "Settings / About device / status" area of your phone . You don't have to click on anything on the page, just look at it!! There you should find your current signal strength level displayed. And once you exit, signal strength widgets will now work. If you reboot your phone you will have to revisit the status section of your phone. A real easy work around that works for me, and maybe you too.
